SALMONELLOSIS - ITALY (02): (ROME), ASIAN FOOD, BACKGROUND
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 23 Jul 2012
Source: Gideon [edited]
http://www.GideonOnline.com


The following background data on salmonellosis in Italy are abstracted from Gideon (http://www.GideonOnline.com) and the Gideon e-book series (1,2) (Primary references available on request):

Since 1990, decreasing rates of salmonellosis in Italy have been paralleled by a relative decrease in cases caused by _S._ Enteritidis; see graph (3) in http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Salm-Italy.png.

The number of salmonellosis outbreaks has also declined, from a high of 552 (3495 cases) in 1992, to 107 (575 cases) in 2010.

Prevalence surveys:
-19.2 percent of childhood diarrhea episodes in Italy
-7.3 percent of pediatric hospitalizations for diarrhea in Rome (1985 publication)
-22.9 percent of children with gastroenteritis presenting to a single hospital (Sondrio Province, Lombardi, 2003 to 2006)
-34 percent of foodborne outbreaks in the Piedmont region (1250 outbreaks of salmonellosis during 2002 to 2009)
-11.1 percent of patients with acute diarrhea (2005)
-0 percent of cheeses (2004)
-0 percent of ready-to-eat salads from process lots (2006 to 2008)
-2.2 percent of foods of animal origin (2001 to 2002)

Notable outbreaks in, or originating in, Italy:
-1966 (publication year) - An outbreak of typhoid (302 cases) and other salmonelloses (60 cases) was reported.
-1966 - An outbreak of _S._ Typhimurium infection was reported in Biella.
-1974 (publication year) - An outbreak of _S._ Agona infection was reported.
-1974 (publication year) - An outbreak of _S._ Typhimurium infection was reported.
-1974 (publication year) - An outbreak of _S._ Enteritidis infection was reported in the area of Paterno (Catania).
-1975 - An outbreak (23 cases) of _S._ Oranienburg infection in Rome was associated with a commercial air flight.
-1982 - An outbreak (245 cases) of _S._ Napoli infection in UK was caused by contaminated chocolate bars imported from Italy.
-1987 - An outbreak of _S._ Typhimurium infection was reported in Palermo.
-1987 - 2 outbreaks of _S._ Kottbus infection were reported in Lombardy.
-1987 to 1988 - An outbreak (110 cases) of _S._ Wien infection was reported in a neonatal unit in Palermo.
-1987 to 1988 - An outbreak of _S._ Typhimurium infections in Isernia was related to consumption of sausage.
-1989 to 1991 - Outbreaks of _S._ Bovismorbificans were reported in southern Italy.
-1991 - Outbreaks of egg-related _S._ Enteritidis infection were reported in northern and central Italy.
-1993 (publication year) - An outbreak of _S._ Enteritidis infection was reported in a nursing home.
-1994 - An outbreak (448 cases) of _S._ Hadar infection was associated with a canteen at a building site in central Italy.
-1995 - An outbreak (83 cases) of _S._ Typhimurium infection in the Lombardy region was ascribed to contaminated salami.
-1997 - An outbreak (29 cases, 12 hospitalized, 1 fatal) of _S._ Hadar infection was reported from a restaurant in Rimini ascribed to roast rabbit.
-1997 - An outbreak of _S._ Enteritidis PT3 infection was reported in northeastern Sardinia.
-1998 (publication year) - An outbreak of _S._ Enteritidis PT4 infection in southern Italy was related to consumption of an egg-based dessert.
-1998 - An outbreak (7 infants) of _S._ Bongori infection was reported in Sicily - source unknown.
-1998 - An outbreak (9 cases) of _S._ Enteritidis infection was related to consumption of a commercially produced cheese.
-1998 - An outbreak (13 cases) of _S._ Blockley infection in Germany was caused by eel imported from Italy.
-1998 - An outbreak (several hundred cases) of _S._ Enteritidis infection in Benvenuto was associated with iced cake served at a religious festival.
-1998 - An outbreak of _S._ Enteritidis infection among Japanese travelers returning from Italy was related to consumption of scrambled eggs in a hotel in Rome.
-2000 (publication year) - An outbreak (113 cases) of _S._ Enteritidis infection in Bari was associated with an egg-based ice cream served at a wedding party.
-2004 - An outbreak (63 cases) of _S._ Typhimurium DT 104A infection in the Rome region was associated with traditional pork salami.
-2005 - An outbreak (22 cases) of _S._ Typhimurium DT 104 infection in Denmark was caused by raw beef carpacio imported from Italy.
-2005 - An outbreak (153 cases) of _S._ Enteritidis infection was reported among school children in Florence.
-2005 - An outbreak of _S._ Enteritidis infection in Bari was ascribed to contaminated rice balls.
-2006 - An outbreak (13 cases) of _S._ Typhimurium infection in Sweden was caused by contaminated salami imported from Italy.
-2007 - An outbreak (56 cases) of salmonellosis related to contaminated spaghetti at a hotel in Spain involved tourists from France, Italy, Spain, Romania, Czech Republic and Albania.
-2007 - An outbreak (16 cases) of _S._ Enteritidis infection in Sicily was associated with eggs used to prepare pastry for a barbecue.
-2008 - An outbreak (30 cases) of salmonellosis was reported among British tourists at a hotel in Brescia.
-2010 - An outbreak (500 cases) of salmonellosis in France was related to ingestion of contaminated hamburger imported from Italy.
-2011 - An outbreak of _S._ Strathcona infections in Denmark (43 cases), Germany (14 cases) and Austria (1 case) was related to contaminated tomatoes imported from Italy.
-2012 (publication year) - An outbreak of _S._ Berta infection was reported.

References:
1. Berger SA: Infectious Diseases of Italy, 2012. 486 pages, 113 graphs, 2696 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-italy/.
2. Berger SA: Salmonellosis: Global Status.; Gideon e-books, 252 pages, 300 graphs, 2297 references. http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/salmonellosis-global-status/.
3. Gideon graph tool at http://www.GIDEONonline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Gideon-Graphs.pps.

